##"MOM's out of the hospital. My Dad's dead. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Citizens of Qingshan District, Wuhan, Wuhan, Ms. Xia

The paper's reporter, Sasha Szeto, collates

Xia Lives in Qingshan District, Wuhan, Wuhan. There are seven people in her family: Her in-laws, her parents, her husband, and her three-year-old child. Earlier, the paper reported that seven members of her family were suspected to have contracted new coronary pneumonia.

Her in-laws, her husband has been found lung infection or disease, was admitted to the Ninth Hospital in Wuhan Isolation Ward. Her parents, who also had lung infections, had been treated at a Central Hospital in Wuhan. Subsequently, her in-laws, husband and mother tested positive for the new coronavirus nucleic acid.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xia's 10 CT report showed that "reexamination has a trend of improvement. ". All images in this post are courtesy of Xia

On the morning of February 4, the 60-year-old father in hospital treatment during the "sudden serious illness" died, she and her family could not see his last face. At the end of January, Ms. Xia was diagnosed with a lung infection. On February 4, she was admitted to a bed waiting for her at Wuhan Central Hospital.

On Feb. 11, Ms. Xia said her mother had recovered and was released from the hospital on the morning of Feb. 11. After the mother was released from the hospital, she learned that her father had died. She cried and cried.

The paper will continue to keep a diary of what Xia's family went through during the treatment.

Here is MS Xia's diary:

Tuesday, February 11th, cloudy

Today is the eighth day of my hospital treatment. I feel hungry every day. I start to be hungry before meal time. Fortunately, a friend brought me congee and soup, the hospital's lunch box, I can add some nutrition.

Actually the family also sent some cookies and snacks, but I do not want to eat these, I think to eat some natural health food to help the body absorb, do not add to the body burden.

This morning, I took five tubes of blood to double-check, and I found some liver function abnormalities. Well, this damn virus seems to be attacking my Zang-fu all over again, and I'm not giving in!

I had a CT scan yesterday, and it came back today, and it said, "I'm on the mend. " I was in a good mood, and I ate more food.

Today, my mother recovered well and has been discharged from hospital. Although she still has a little cough, it should get better gradually.

Before, my family kept the news of my father's death a secret from my mother. When she got out of the hospital, she asked where my dad was staying and wanted to see him. I can't hide it now. I told her the truth. She was crying and crying, and she was crying when I called her just now.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ms. Xia's long-disinfected hands.

I know it's hard for her to accept that, but we just have to move on. This period of time, my family of seven have experienced too much pain, I think I am still strong. I comforted my mother, "at the moment, the family is in the hospital, we have to take care of their own body. "

February 11,2020

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
